      {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13112390/comment/16261167",
        "id": "16261167",
        "author": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=billie",
          "name": "billie",
          "key": "billie.rinaldi",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=billie.rinaldi&avatarId=30233",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=billie.rinaldi&avatarId=30233",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=billie.rinaldi&avatarId=30233",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=billie.rinaldi&avatarId=30233"
          },
          "displayName": "Billie Rinaldi",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/New_York"
        },
        "body": "[~eyang], thanks for providing the image, it makes the goals very clear.\r\n\r\nWhat would the ServiceTemplate look like? I assume the recommended templates are for displaying in the UI. How are recommended templates populated (that is, do we need a method for adding service templates for the recommended list)? Will all users have the same recommended templates?\r\n\r\nFor the update methods, will we provide a way to merge the Service/ServiceTemplate into an existing service, or will it just overwrite the existing one? If it is overwriting, perhaps put would be a better name for the methods. Would it make sense to support versioning of Service or ServiceTemplate objects? We don't do that now, so it could be left for future discussion/implementation.\r\n\r\nDo the get/update/remove methods refer to one service instance? In this case they should have a user parameter as well?",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=billie",
          "name": "billie",
          "key": "billie.rinaldi",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=billie.rinaldi&avatarId=30233",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=billie.rinaldi&avatarId=30233",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=billie.rinaldi&avatarId=30233",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=billie.rinaldi&avatarId=30233"
          },
          "displayName": "Billie Rinaldi",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/New_York"
        },
        "created": "2017-11-21T17:57:26.801+0000",
        "updated": "2017-11-21T17:57:26.801+0000"
      },
      {
        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13112390/comment/16261337",
        "id": "16261337",
        "author": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=eyang",
          "name": "eyang",
          "key": "eyang",
          "avatarUrls": {
            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
          },
          "displayName": "Eric Yang",
          "active": true,
          "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
        },
        "body": "Hi [~billie.rinaldi], YARN-7523 has a proposal for refining Service object.  It will be a great opportunity to add the metadata fields, such as organization, description, and fields into the ServiceTemplate object.  All users will start out using the recommended templates, then tweak the configuration to match their specific requirements.  ServiceTemplate changes will apply to new instance of application to deploy.  Existed service has taken life of its own.  It will not be changed by ServiceTemplate changes.  Update method is really an overwrite.  I will rename update to save for correctness.  @Gour Saha is adding version field into both Service and ServiceTemplate object in YARN-7512.\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\nDo the get/update/remove methods refer to one service instance? In this case they should have a user parameter as well?\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nYes, this make sense.  I will pass UGI parameter to the interface.  I think Service object also need to include user information for identifying the original user.  UGI parameter and stored user information needs to match to allow performing an operation for centralized metadata storage.  Thank you for the review.",
        "updateAuthor": {
          "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=eyang",
          "name": "eyang",
          "key": "eyang",
          "avatarUrls": {
